## EmailJS Environment Example
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your EmailJS keys

# EmailJS service (Dashboard → Email Services → Service ID)
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_xxxxx   # e.g., service_abc123

# EmailJS template (Dashboard → Email Templates → Template ID)
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxx # (Contact form) e.g., template_123abc

# EmailJS public key (Dashboard → Account → API Keys → Public Key)
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=public_xxxxx    # e.g., XyZabc123ABC

# Optional: a dedicated Apply form template
# If you already created one named "Job Application" with id template_fq4q7xv, put it here:
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_APPLY_TEMPLATE_ID=template_fq4q7xv

# Notes:
# - Add your allowed domains in EmailJS (Account → Domains), e.g. http://localhost:3000 and https://thehillengroup.net
# - In your EmailJS Contact template, include variables: {{name}}, {{email}}, {{company}}, {{subject}}, {{message}}
# - In your EmailJS Apply template, include: {{name}}, {{email}}, {{location}}, {{linkedin}}, {{portfolio}},
#   {{subject}}, {{message}}, {{jobId}}, {{jobTitle}}, {{page}}. File uploads are attached automatically via sendForm.
# - Set Reply-To to {{email}} and From to a fixed address on your domain for better deliverability.
